  "prompt": "How can I use AutoCAD on my Chromebook?",
  "response": "There are several ways to use AutoCAD on a Chromebook:\n\n1. Online/Cloud-based Options:\n- AutoCAD Web: Official web version accessible through a browser\n- Fusion 360 Web: Cloud-based CAD software\n- AutoCAD mobile app (limited functionality)\n\n2. Linux (Beta) Method:\n- Enable Linux on your Chromebook\n- Use Wine or CrossOver to run Windows version of AutoCAD\n- Requires compatible Chromebook with Linux support\n\n3. Remote Desktop Solutions:\n- Use Remote Desktop apps like Chrome Remote Desktop\n- Connect to a Windows computer with AutoCAD installed\n- Stream AutoCAD from another device\n\n4. Cloud-based Virtual Desktop:\n- Use cloud computing services like Amazon WorkSpaces\n- Run AutoCAD through a virtual Windows environment\n- Requires subscription and good internet connection\n\n5. Alternative CAD Software:\n- Onshape (web-based CAD)\n- SketchUp Free\n- FreeCAD (open-source)\n\nMost recommended options:\n- AutoCAD Web\n- Fusion 360 Web\n- Remote Desktop connection\n\nNote: Full AutoCAD functionality might be limited on Chromebooks due to hardware and software constraints.",
